1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 1=
(Breathe)

3
00:01:40,024 --> 00:01:41,104
(Hand in hand,)

4
00:01:41,303 --> 00:01:44,503
(they stepped into
their own secret realm.)

5
00:01:46,783 --> 00:01:51,104
(Guided by memory, they searched
for the leopard seen that morning.)

6
00:01:53,143 --> 00:01:56,184
(Death buried their youth.)

7
00:01:57,303 --> 00:02:00,624
(But terror would haunt them for life.)

8
00:02:00,624 --> 00:02:01,904
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2023)

9
00:02:01,904 --> 00:02:08,743
(Terror would brand their souls,
leaving a unique and indelible mark,)

10
00:02:09,264 --> 00:02:10,224
(until death.)

11
00:02:11,104 --> 00:02:13,784
(Qingzhou)
These two girls are full of stories.

12
00:02:14,023 --> 00:02:16,463
(Book Launch: "Breathe" by Liu Xiaoran)
Who knows what secrets still lie hidden?

13
00:02:16,784 --> 00:02:18,423
Read on, and discover the truth.

14
00:02:19,143 --> 00:02:22,623
Welcome to the book launch
of Liu Xiaoran's new work, "Breathe."

15
00:02:23,264 --> 00:02:26,944
"Dedicated to my beloved
Ms. Ren Xiaoming."

16
00:02:27,303 --> 00:02:29,824
I heard every book of yours
starts with this line.

17
00:02:30,664 --> 00:02:31,264
That's right.

18
00:02:31,423 --> 00:02:35,984
She is the most important person to me.

19
00:02:40,088 --> 00:02:40,792
(Liu Xiaoran)

20
00:02:50,703 --> 00:02:52,384
(She will always be my first reader)

21
00:02:52,944 --> 00:02:54,303
(Book Launch: "Breathe" by Liu Xiaoran)
(and my source of inspiration.)

22
00:02:54,984 --> 00:02:56,743
(Yide Law Firm)
(This book is dedicated to her)

23
00:02:57,023 --> 00:02:59,423
(and tells her life story.)

24
00:03:04,344 --> 00:03:05,344
I'm suing Liu Xiaoran.

25
00:03:08,544 --> 00:03:10,664
Last night's recording. Listen to it.

26
00:03:14,623 --> 00:03:15,183
Liu Xiaoran.

27
00:03:15,423 --> 00:03:16,303
(The night before)
Talk to him.

28
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:17,984
Hurry up.

29
00:03:20,824 --> 00:03:22,023
Zhang, it's me.

30
00:03:22,264 --> 00:03:25,384
Mr. Liu? Why are you
using Xiaoming's phone?

31
00:03:25,984 --> 00:03:27,504
She's sulking.

32
00:03:28,064 --> 00:03:29,023
What happened?

33
00:03:29,623 --> 00:03:30,463
Well, you know.

34
00:03:32,023 --> 00:03:34,544
She read "Breathe"
and insists we recall the book.

35
00:03:36,423 --> 00:03:37,224
Mr. Zhang.

36
00:03:38,183 --> 00:03:38,824
It's Xiaoming.

37
00:03:39,703 --> 00:03:41,104
You must recall this book.

38
00:03:41,743 --> 00:03:44,088
It's without my permission.
It's a violation of my privacy.

39
00:03:44,504 --> 00:03:48,023
Xiaoming, I'm so sorry.
It's all my fault.

40
00:03:48,143 --> 00:03:52,064
Mr. Liu told me it was your story.

41
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:54,423
There would be no book without you.

42
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:59,824
He wanted to co-author it with you,
but I disagreed.

43
00:04:00,104 --> 00:04:00,903
It's not about that.

44
00:04:00,903 --> 00:04:02,023
- I don't want credit...
- Well...

45
00:04:02,023 --> 00:04:04,784
You're married.
Co-authoring it is unnecessary.

46
00:04:04,903 --> 00:04:06,143
Here's what I think.

47
00:04:06,544 --> 00:04:09,944
The book is printed.
Changing the credit means reprinting.

48
00:04:10,224 --> 00:04:12,023
The cost would be huge.

49
00:04:12,703 --> 00:04:15,944
Our publishing house
has to consider profitability, right?

50
00:04:15,944 --> 00:04:18,503
But he published my story
without my permission.

51
00:04:19,063 --> 00:04:20,224
This is infringement.

52
00:04:20,904 --> 00:04:23,104
You two should work it out yourselves.

53
00:04:26,863 --> 00:04:30,423
See? It's no big deal.
Look how worked up you are.

54
00:04:31,224 --> 00:04:33,263
It's really not necessary.

55
00:04:36,584 --> 00:04:39,503
Anyway, it's all yours.

56
00:04:39,943 --> 00:04:43,224
The money goes to our shared account.
I won't take a cent, okay?

57
00:04:43,743 --> 00:04:47,743
It's not about the money.
You stole my story.

58
00:04:48,623 --> 00:04:49,784
Aren't we married?

59
00:04:49,984 --> 00:04:51,943
Do you have to draw such a clear line?

60
00:04:51,943 --> 00:04:54,943
But you copied the entire story
from my diary.

61
00:04:56,904 --> 00:04:58,784
Liu Xiaoran, search your conscience.

62
00:04:59,383 --> 00:05:01,704
You took my thesis
and all the drafts on my computer.

63
00:05:01,704 --> 00:05:02,623
Did I say anything?

64
00:05:02,823 --> 00:05:05,224
I let you use them
because they meant nothing to me.

65
00:05:05,224 --> 00:05:08,024
But this diary matters so much to me.

66
00:05:08,024 --> 00:05:09,104
You cannot copy it.

67
00:05:13,383 --> 00:05:14,544
Please show some respect.

68
00:05:18,224 --> 00:05:21,664
Xiaoming, I know you're upset.

69
00:05:23,024 --> 00:05:25,423
You can tell me whatever you want

70
00:05:26,664 --> 00:05:29,623
and express your opinions.

71
00:05:34,904 --> 00:05:38,503
But you can't force me

72
00:05:38,584 --> 00:05:41,704
to admit things
I haven't done like this.

73
00:05:42,464 --> 00:05:46,423
Liu Xiaoran, are you denying
that you copied my diary?

74
00:06:01,584 --> 00:06:02,623
We are family.

75
00:06:06,063 --> 00:06:09,144
Building a home
brick by brick isn't easy.

76
00:06:10,344 --> 00:06:14,104
Destroying it
takes only a fleeting thought.

77
00:06:23,984 --> 00:06:24,904
Where's your diary?

78
00:06:25,383 --> 00:06:27,383
I can't find it. Liu Xiaoran hid it.

79
00:06:27,784 --> 00:06:29,984
Then how do you prove
he plagiarized your story?

80
00:06:31,303 --> 00:06:34,823
Any copies, manuscripts,
or email records?

81
00:06:35,104 --> 00:06:35,743
No.

82
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:36,823
Witnesses?

83
00:06:39,743 --> 00:06:40,263
None.

84
00:06:40,503 --> 00:06:42,063
He who asserts must prove.

85
00:06:42,503 --> 00:06:44,743
No evidence, no case.

86
00:06:45,503 --> 00:06:48,503
But most of the plots
are things I personally experienced.

87
00:06:50,104 --> 00:06:51,464
They can be verified.

88
00:06:51,904 --> 00:06:55,344
Content alone can't serve
as direct proof of authorship.

89
00:06:56,943 --> 00:06:59,303
We've been friends for over a decade.
I'll be honest.

90
00:06:59,743 --> 00:07:04,263
You can't sue him
under these circumstances.

91
00:07:05,183 --> 00:07:09,144
(I have proof.
That diary is the best evidence.)

92
00:07:09,464 --> 00:07:12,464
(But even if I find it,
it can't be made public.)

93
00:07:12,743 --> 00:07:14,144
(It must remain a secret.)

94
00:07:20,623 --> 00:07:22,584
(Where did that diary go?)

95
00:07:37,823 --> 00:07:42,224
(I bet Liu Xiaoran hid it.
And he's playing dumb.)

96
00:07:42,623 --> 00:07:44,584
Remember what I said.

97
00:07:44,863 --> 00:07:48,584
Cook with love to keep your loved one.

98
00:07:48,863 --> 00:07:50,904
That's a famous saying...

99
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:54,503
You're back? Xiaoming's back.
We're signing off for today.

100
00:07:54,664 --> 00:07:55,303
Time for dinner.

101
00:07:56,063 --> 00:07:59,704
(Liu Xiaoran's livestream)
Remember my white-cut chicken recipe?

102
00:08:00,224 --> 00:08:02,984
Next time we'll have an exam. Bye.

103
00:08:04,224 --> 00:08:08,024
Wash your hands.
My signature white-cut chicken.

104
00:08:09,303 --> 00:08:13,383
Trying to win me over with a chicken
while streaming?

105
00:08:14,104 --> 00:08:15,183
Two birds with one stone?

106
00:08:15,623 --> 00:08:17,984
The stream was a task
assigned by the platform.

107
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,984
But I made the chicken for you.

108
00:08:21,823 --> 00:08:24,104
You've been working hard lately.

109
00:08:26,263 --> 00:08:27,344
On the copyright battle?

110
00:08:28,743 --> 00:08:31,024
No business talk today. Come on.

111
00:08:32,783 --> 00:08:34,984
Stealing a moment of leisure
in this busy life.

112
00:08:35,263 --> 00:08:38,383
Try the sauce. See if it's too salty.

113
00:08:38,503 --> 00:08:40,824
Beating around the bush, huh?

114
00:08:41,944 --> 00:08:43,383
No voice recorder today.

115
00:08:46,824 --> 00:08:48,064
You went to Liang Yi today?

116
00:08:50,064 --> 00:08:51,104
How did you know?

117
00:08:51,383 --> 00:08:54,224
Aren't you suing me? What did she say?

118
00:08:57,704 --> 00:09:00,424
Wait for the court trial.
She said I'm sure to win.

119
00:09:02,743 --> 00:09:05,743
You're sure to win? Congratulations.

120
00:09:07,863 --> 00:09:09,623
I want my cut. Cash.

121
00:09:11,263 --> 00:09:14,023
Okay, cash. How much?

122
00:09:16,224 --> 00:09:16,863
A hundred grand.

123
00:09:20,383 --> 00:09:22,143
That's all you're asking for?

124
00:09:23,383 --> 00:09:26,863
No need to wait for royalties.
I'll get the cash tomorrow.

125
00:09:27,543 --> 00:09:31,503
Fine, let's sign a contract.
Write it all down.

126
00:09:31,584 --> 00:09:36,224
Liu Xiaoran paid Ren Xiaoming
100 grand RMB for her diary.

127
00:09:39,663 --> 00:09:40,503
What diary?

128
00:09:42,743 --> 00:09:45,424
What diary are you talking about?
Don't set me up.

129
00:09:45,984 --> 00:09:48,143
Mr. Liu, you're way too dramatic.

130
00:09:48,783 --> 00:09:50,064
I'm not recording you.

131
00:09:50,783 --> 00:09:52,623
Even if I were, you don't have to shout.

132
00:09:52,623 --> 00:09:53,663
We're alone here.

133
00:09:54,184 --> 00:09:57,743
Technology has advanced.
Audio recording has improved.

134
00:09:58,383 --> 00:10:00,344
If one day you dare to tell the truth,

135
00:10:00,863 --> 00:10:02,903
it will be recorded
even if it's just a whisper.

136
00:10:04,824 --> 00:10:05,944
Where's the diary?

137
00:10:08,704 --> 00:10:09,543
Stop pretending.

138
00:10:11,263 --> 00:10:12,184
Where did you hide it?

139
00:10:15,424 --> 00:10:19,863
The chicken's good.
But the chef is too scheming.

140
00:10:21,783 --> 00:10:22,783
It's overcooked.

141
00:10:46,383 --> 00:10:46,903
Oh right.

142
00:10:52,023 --> 00:10:53,304
Your mom called me today,

143
00:10:53,663 --> 00:10:56,503
asking if I'm going with you
to her wedding tomorrow.

144
00:10:56,824 --> 00:11:00,623
I didn't tell her for sure.
I said I needed to ask you.

145
00:11:01,104 --> 00:11:04,623
After all, you never wanted me
involved in your family matters.

146
00:11:05,104 --> 00:11:07,984
It has nothing to do with you.
You don't need to go.

147
00:11:08,344 --> 00:11:08,944
Okay.

148
00:11:10,383 --> 00:11:11,704
Is this her fourth marriage?

149
00:11:14,304 --> 00:11:14,863
Why?

150
00:11:16,304 --> 00:11:18,023
Just asking. Never mind.

151
00:11:19,304 --> 00:11:22,584
You should check, though,
if the groom's surname is Li.

152
00:11:23,743 --> 00:11:26,104
What do you mean?
What about his surname?

153
00:11:26,584 --> 00:11:29,863
Your biological dad is a Zhao.
She divorced him and remarried a Qian.

154
00:11:30,224 --> 00:11:32,104
After Qian died, she married a Sun.

155
00:11:33,623 --> 00:11:38,424
Following the hundred surnames,
Zhao, Qian, Sun, and Li.

156
00:11:39,344 --> 00:11:42,503
Next should be Li, right?

157
00:11:45,424 --> 00:11:48,383
Just kidding. Here's what I think.

158
00:11:48,863 --> 00:11:51,184
I won't give you 100 grand directly.

159
00:11:51,383 --> 00:11:55,104
I'll wire it to your mom
as a gesture from both of us.

160
00:11:55,584 --> 00:11:57,543
I'll take you to the airport
tomorrow morning.

161
00:11:58,143 --> 00:11:59,383
Leave me alone, thief.

162
00:12:02,224 --> 00:12:02,984
If you need me...

163
00:12:02,984 --> 00:12:03,743
No, I don't.

164
00:12:15,263 --> 00:12:16,143
Dead?

165
00:12:17,984 --> 00:12:21,143
I told you not to mess around.
Now you're dead.

166
00:12:32,536 --> 00:12:35,672
(Groom: Li Wancheng, Bride: Ren Meiyan
We're getting married!)

167
00:12:35,672 --> 00:12:38,328
(Holding your hand,
growing old together)

168
00:12:44,143 --> 00:12:47,783
Ren Meiyan is married four times
because she's pretty.

169
00:12:48,263 --> 00:12:51,184
You know what, her son is mental,

170
00:12:51,344 --> 00:12:52,704
and she has a tagalong.

171
00:12:53,023 --> 00:12:54,064
(It really is a Li.)

172
00:12:54,064 --> 00:12:55,344
(Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.)

173
00:12:55,543 --> 00:12:57,984
(Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.)

174
00:12:58,104 --> 00:12:59,783
(Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.)

175
00:12:59,944 --> 00:13:01,304
(1996, Qidaohezi)
(Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.)

176
00:13:01,304 --> 00:13:01,824
Zhang Fang.

177
00:13:01,824 --> 00:13:03,023
Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.

178
00:13:03,224 --> 00:13:04,663
Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.

179
00:13:04,863 --> 00:13:06,224
Ren Xiaoming, the tagalong.

180
00:13:08,584 --> 00:13:13,584
Ren Xiaoming. How dare you kick me!
I'll make you pay.

181
00:13:13,663 --> 00:13:16,424
Zhang Fang! Stop yelling in the yard.

182
00:13:17,064 --> 00:13:19,184
I can't even take a nap.
All I hear is your shout.

183
00:13:19,503 --> 00:13:20,743
The tagalong hit me with rocks.

184
00:13:20,743 --> 00:13:22,984
Serves you right.
Why did you call her a tagalong?

185
00:13:23,184 --> 00:13:24,344
You called her that first.

186
00:13:26,503 --> 00:13:28,503
Xiaoming, I didn't.

187
00:13:29,104 --> 00:13:31,184
You did. You told Dad
that her mom brought

188
00:13:31,184 --> 00:13:32,184
two tagalongs

189
00:13:32,263 --> 00:13:35,184
and if he even looked at her mom,
you'd gouge his eyes out.

190
00:13:35,184 --> 00:13:35,783
Shut up.

191
00:13:37,224 --> 00:13:38,143
You rascal.

192
00:13:39,224 --> 00:13:42,304
Xiaoming, Auntie didn't say that.

193
00:13:42,503 --> 00:13:45,824
Xiaoming, don't tell your mom.
Auntie didn't say that.

194
00:13:46,704 --> 00:13:49,503
What are you staring at?
You rascal, stay right there!

195
00:13:51,143 --> 00:13:52,184
I'm so sorry.

196
00:13:52,184 --> 00:13:53,064
It's fine.

197
00:13:53,064 --> 00:13:55,984
It's your first time visiting,
and I made you fix this and that.

198
00:13:56,023 --> 00:13:56,704
It's fine.

199
00:13:59,224 --> 00:14:00,824
I used to be an electrician.

200
00:14:01,224 --> 00:14:03,064
It took you so long
to get some soy sauce?

201
00:14:05,383 --> 00:14:06,383
It's the connection.

202
00:14:07,143 --> 00:14:07,903
Really?

203
00:14:09,984 --> 00:14:13,783
I'm raising a daughter alone
with no one to count on.

204
00:14:15,263 --> 00:14:16,383
Liar.

205
00:14:16,883 --> 00:14:17,383
It's on.

206
00:14:17,383 --> 00:14:18,023
Done.

207
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:18,783
You fixed it.

208
00:14:18,783 --> 00:14:20,584
Yeah, it was a loose connection.

209
00:14:21,064 --> 00:14:21,743
Alright.

210
00:14:21,743 --> 00:14:23,184
Done.

211
00:14:24,304 --> 00:14:25,143
Take a break.

212
00:14:25,184 --> 00:14:25,863
- Give it to me.
- Here.

213
00:14:25,863 --> 00:14:26,543
- No.
- Give it to me.

214
00:14:26,543 --> 00:14:27,184
Leave it here.

215
00:14:27,304 --> 00:14:28,944
Sit down and rest a bit.

216
00:14:29,224 --> 00:14:32,023
Feel free to tell me
whenever you need help.

217
00:14:32,263 --> 00:14:33,704
I can do anything.

218
00:14:34,424 --> 00:14:36,743
My gas stove won't light.

219
00:14:37,383 --> 00:14:38,143
- Gas stove?
- Sit.

220
00:14:38,143 --> 00:14:38,824
- Take a break.
- It's fine.

221
00:14:38,824 --> 00:14:40,783
I can fix it.
I used to work with gas, too.

222
00:14:41,503 --> 00:14:43,263
You know gas pipelines, too?

223
00:14:45,263 --> 00:14:47,863
Kiddo, help yourself
to the snacks on the table.

224
00:14:48,023 --> 00:14:51,064
Did you hear him?
Uncle Qian brought you some cookies.

225
00:14:51,383 --> 00:14:52,944
- Something's stuck inside.
- Really?

226
00:14:53,023 --> 00:14:53,623
(Award)
It's stuck.

227
00:14:56,143 --> 00:14:56,783
Probably.

228
00:14:58,263 --> 00:14:58,783
Hold on.

229
00:15:00,344 --> 00:15:01,263
Got gas now.

230
00:15:02,143 --> 00:15:03,224
- Magic hands.
- Easy peasy.

231
00:15:03,304 --> 00:15:04,903
You fixed it just like that.

232
00:15:05,543 --> 00:15:08,224
The drain for the washbasin is clogged.

233
00:15:08,224 --> 00:15:08,903
Really?

234
00:15:08,984 --> 00:15:10,104
This drain is clogged.

235
00:15:10,104 --> 00:15:10,903
- No problem.
- Look.

236
00:15:10,903 --> 00:15:11,543
Let me see.

237
00:15:11,623 --> 00:15:13,224
I used to do plumbing, too.

238
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:14,783
(White rice vinegar)
Let me find you a tool.

239
00:15:14,863 --> 00:15:15,383
Got one?

240
00:15:18,424 --> 00:15:19,503
It looks loose.

241
00:15:19,503 --> 00:15:20,743
Pry this part a bit.

242
00:15:21,304 --> 00:15:23,383
Just put it back on. Here.

243
00:15:24,184 --> 00:15:25,383
- Keep an eye on it.
- Okay.

244
00:15:25,383 --> 00:15:26,344
(White rice vinegar)

245
00:15:26,344 --> 00:15:26,844
Done.

246
00:15:27,424 --> 00:15:28,263
You made it?

247
00:15:28,304 --> 00:15:28,903
Yeah.

248
00:15:29,263 --> 00:15:30,064
(Award)
All set.

249
00:15:31,143 --> 00:15:31,704
Done.

250
00:15:31,824 --> 00:15:33,824
- It's working.
- You made it.

251
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:36,184
It's okay now.

252
00:15:36,184 --> 00:15:37,064
It's fixed.

253
00:15:37,584 --> 00:15:38,184
- Done.
- Yeah.

254
00:15:38,184 --> 00:15:38,824
It's okay now.

255
00:15:38,903 --> 00:15:40,304
- Thank you.
- No problem.

256
00:15:40,503 --> 00:15:42,863
You know, Meiyan, I've also done masonry

257
00:15:42,863 --> 00:15:43,984
and carpentry work.

258
00:15:44,224 --> 00:15:45,863
I can even fix leaks.

259
00:15:46,503 --> 00:15:47,783
So versatile?

260
00:15:48,543 --> 00:15:49,383
Have some dumplings.

261
00:15:49,484 --> 00:15:49,984
No need.

262
00:15:49,984 --> 00:15:51,064
Try my cooking.

263
00:15:51,104 --> 00:15:52,263
- Dumplings.
- You're too kind.

264
00:15:52,424 --> 00:15:53,743
It will take only a second.

265
00:15:53,743 --> 00:15:55,104
- No rush.
- Wait for me.

266
00:15:55,104 --> 00:15:55,903
Alright.

267
00:16:17,783 --> 00:16:18,344
Well...

268
00:16:20,263 --> 00:16:23,224
Meiyan, I should head back first.

269
00:16:23,623 --> 00:16:24,424
Already?

270
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:28,383
I just remembered
that my bike probably needs fixing.

271
00:16:28,824 --> 00:16:29,503
I have to do.

272
00:16:30,984 --> 00:16:31,503
Alright.

273
00:16:31,663 --> 00:16:32,584
I'm still cooking.

274
00:16:32,584 --> 00:16:34,023
- It's okay. Next time.
- Zhongshi.

275
00:16:34,023 --> 00:16:34,623
Next time.

276
00:16:34,623 --> 00:16:35,543
Come again, Zhongshi.

277
00:16:35,543 --> 00:16:36,503
Next time.

278
00:16:41,863 --> 00:16:43,128
You broke the vinegar bottle?

279
00:16:44,783 --> 00:16:45,663
No.

280
00:16:46,304 --> 00:16:47,344
Then why does it smell?

281
00:16:48,743 --> 00:16:51,143
Pick up your brother
from Granny Sun's house.

282
00:16:51,224 --> 00:16:52,184
"Your brother."

283
00:16:53,064 --> 00:16:54,424
You're a liar.

284
00:16:54,863 --> 00:16:56,543
Why didn't you tell him you have a son?

285
00:16:56,704 --> 00:16:57,224
I...

286
00:16:58,503 --> 00:17:00,104
I have a son and a daughter. So what?

287
00:17:09,263 --> 00:17:12,464
Don't come again. My mom lied to you.

288
00:17:13,704 --> 00:17:16,543
She has two children.
I have a younger brother.

289
00:17:17,543 --> 00:17:20,944
He has a mental illness
and needs a lot of money for treatment.

290
00:17:21,303 --> 00:17:22,743
My dad couldn't afford it and left.

291
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:28,503
Getting along well
with your new dad, huh?

292
00:17:29,343 --> 00:17:30,624
Ren Xiaoming, tagalong.

293
00:17:30,823 --> 00:17:32,224
Ren Xiaoming, tagalong.

294
00:17:32,864 --> 00:17:33,384
Get lost.

295
00:17:38,303 --> 00:17:39,224
Don't be mad.

296
00:17:39,503 --> 00:17:41,664
I will definitely beat him up.
He won't get away.

297
00:17:41,944 --> 00:17:42,783
Don't be mad.

298
00:17:53,184 --> 00:17:53,823
Xiaoming.

299
00:18:06,864 --> 00:18:09,904
(That was the day
he decided to marry my mom)

300
00:18:10,624 --> 00:18:12,184
(and become my second dad.)

301
00:18:15,224 --> 00:18:18,144
(His surname was Qian.
Full name, Qian Zhongshi.)

302
00:18:26,503 --> 00:18:27,144
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

303
00:18:34,343 --> 00:18:35,303
Be careful.

304
00:18:45,543 --> 00:18:47,023
Here comes the groom!

305
00:18:50,424 --> 00:18:51,743
Have some candy.

306
00:18:53,503 --> 00:18:54,184
Thank you.

307
00:18:54,184 --> 00:18:54,704
Cheapskate.

308
00:18:55,263 --> 00:18:57,184
Meiyan, let's go home.

309
00:18:59,103 --> 00:19:00,583
- He's getting shy.
- Thank you.

310
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:03,144
Ren Xiaoming,
will you come back to play with me?

311
00:19:03,704 --> 00:19:05,783
You're acting all mighty
in those new clothes?

312
00:19:05,944 --> 00:19:06,583
Get lost.

313
00:19:07,023 --> 00:19:08,023
Goodbye forever.

314
00:19:08,624 --> 00:19:09,343
So petty.

315
00:19:09,664 --> 00:19:11,424
Stop pulling me. Go to Mom.

316
00:19:15,624 --> 00:19:18,023
Xiaofei, come on, get in the car.

317
00:19:18,503 --> 00:19:20,503
Come on. One, two, three, get in.

318
00:19:21,103 --> 00:19:23,503
Xiaoming, come on, let's go home.

319
00:19:23,783 --> 00:19:26,303
Come on.

320
00:19:27,823 --> 00:19:28,503
Come on.

321
00:19:34,864 --> 00:19:35,503
Thank you.

322
00:19:35,503 --> 00:19:36,103
Maiden home.

323
00:19:36,103 --> 00:19:38,624
Thank you.

324
00:19:39,003 --> 00:19:39,503
Don't worry.

325
00:19:39,503 --> 00:19:41,063
- Come visit.
- Okay.

326
00:19:41,063 --> 00:19:41,904
- Bye.
- Bye.

327
00:19:41,944 --> 00:19:43,543
Bye. Thank you.

328
00:19:43,704 --> 00:19:45,144
Alright.

329
00:19:47,343 --> 00:19:49,583
(The neighbors' blessings
were her only dowry.)

330
00:19:50,743 --> 00:19:54,503
(In my memory,
this was her most splendid wedding.)

331
00:19:55,224 --> 00:19:57,664
Thank you.

332
00:19:57,864 --> 00:20:00,343
Take your seats. Have fun.

333
00:20:00,864 --> 00:20:01,704
Where is Liu Xiaoran?

334
00:20:02,144 --> 00:20:02,783
He didn't come.

335
00:20:03,224 --> 00:20:04,543
He said he'd come on the phone.

336
00:20:04,543 --> 00:20:06,103
Can you stop calling him?

337
00:20:06,303 --> 00:20:07,904
Why can't I call my son-in-law?

338
00:20:09,783 --> 00:20:10,704
Congratulations.

339
00:20:10,864 --> 00:20:11,984
Thank you.

340
00:20:11,984 --> 00:20:12,904
Congratulations.

341
00:20:13,023 --> 00:20:14,343
This is my daughter.

342
00:20:14,343 --> 00:20:15,424
You're so blessed.

343
00:20:15,424 --> 00:20:19,664
My son-in-law is Liu Xiaoran,
a famous writer and professor.

344
00:20:19,664 --> 00:20:20,704
You're so blessed.

345
00:20:20,704 --> 00:20:23,063
How is she blessed? It's embarrassing.

346
00:20:23,303 --> 00:20:25,624
She's just scrounging for meals
with a tagalong.

347
00:20:25,704 --> 00:20:26,664
What are you saying?

348
00:20:26,984 --> 00:20:28,944
I didn't say that. They did.

349
00:20:29,464 --> 00:20:31,583
No, we didn't.

350
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:32,503
- I didn't.
- Of course, you did.

351
00:20:32,503 --> 00:20:34,543
Why did you say that
on such a happy day?

352
00:20:34,823 --> 00:20:36,984
My banquet is priced per head.

353
00:20:36,984 --> 00:20:37,783
The gift money?

354
00:20:38,944 --> 00:20:39,444
Here.

355
00:20:39,563 --> 00:20:40,063
That's all?

356
00:20:40,063 --> 00:20:41,503
Meiyan, I have to go, too.

357
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:42,664
Where's your gift money?

358
00:20:45,464 --> 00:20:45,984
Thanks.

359
00:20:46,103 --> 00:20:47,664
- So annoying.
- So annoying.

360
00:20:47,664 --> 00:20:48,624
- Wait for me.
- Ignore them.

361
00:20:48,624 --> 00:20:49,464
Ignore them.

362
00:20:49,464 --> 00:20:52,823
Easy. Be seated and have fun.

363
00:20:52,823 --> 00:20:53,704
Have a seat.

364
00:20:53,743 --> 00:20:57,624
You'll let people call you anything
for that little money, won't you?

365
00:20:57,783 --> 00:20:59,263
Pay if you want to criticize me.

366
00:21:05,864 --> 00:21:07,464
Do you remember what day it is today?

367
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:11,384
(1996, Qidaohezi)

368
00:21:11,384 --> 00:21:11,944
Qian Xiaofei.

369
00:21:12,184 --> 00:21:12,864
Qian Xiaofei.

370
00:21:12,864 --> 00:21:14,424
Qian Xiaofei.

371
00:21:15,783 --> 00:21:17,303
Qian Xiaoming.

372
00:21:17,384 --> 00:21:19,944
Qian Xiaoming.

373
00:21:21,503 --> 00:21:24,944
Alright, I have both a son
and a daughter now.

374
00:21:38,184 --> 00:21:39,864
Xiaoming, what are you doing?

375
00:21:40,144 --> 00:21:41,783
None of your business. Go play.

376
00:21:44,144 --> 00:21:45,424
(Household registration)
Qian.

377
00:21:45,864 --> 00:21:49,023
I don't want his surname.
Who is Qian Xiaoming?

378
00:21:49,783 --> 00:21:52,823
Why did you scratch up
the household registration booklet?

379
00:21:57,904 --> 00:21:59,583
I'm back.

380
00:22:01,464 --> 00:22:02,864
Qian Xiaofei.

381
00:22:06,624 --> 00:22:08,023
Qian Xiaoming.

382
00:22:10,424 --> 00:22:12,944
Qian Xiaoming, what are you hiding?

383
00:22:14,704 --> 00:22:16,696
She doesn't want that name

384
00:22:16,696 --> 00:22:19,343
and scratched up her name
on the household registration booklet.

385
00:22:19,904 --> 00:22:20,664
Give it to me.

386
00:22:22,103 --> 00:22:22,823
Give it to me.

387
00:22:23,583 --> 00:22:25,664
You married him.
But I didn't want a new dad.

388
00:22:28,144 --> 00:22:30,503
I swear I'll beat you to death today.

389
00:22:31,184 --> 00:22:31,783
What's wrong?

390
00:22:32,144 --> 00:22:32,644
Come here.

391
00:22:32,864 --> 00:22:33,783
- She scratched it up.
- Stop.

392
00:22:33,783 --> 00:22:34,464
Easy now.

393
00:22:34,543 --> 00:22:35,904
Meiyan, put your shoe on first.

394
00:22:35,984 --> 00:22:36,783
- Outrageous.
- Come on.

395
00:22:36,783 --> 00:22:37,624
Put your shoe on.

396
00:22:37,624 --> 00:22:41,384
If she doesn't want that last name,
nor do I.

397
00:22:43,783 --> 00:22:45,823
Rock-paper-scissors.

398
00:22:45,904 --> 00:22:48,384
Rock-paper-scissors.

399
00:22:50,144 --> 00:22:51,424
The tagalong is back.

400
00:22:52,184 --> 00:22:53,464
Your new dad didn't want you?

401
00:22:54,023 --> 00:22:55,063
Watch your mouth.

402
00:22:55,103 --> 00:22:56,303
What's wrong with you?

403
00:22:57,464 --> 00:22:58,543
You hit me?

404
00:23:00,303 --> 00:23:02,503
Stop messing with me.

405
00:23:04,624 --> 00:23:07,624
If you bully my daughter again,
I'll break your legs.

406
00:23:09,184 --> 00:23:09,684
Get lost.

407
00:23:13,424 --> 00:23:16,424
I'll get even with you.
Just wait, tagalong.

408
00:23:53,704 --> 00:23:56,023
Sweetie, let's go home.

409
00:23:56,743 --> 00:23:59,743
Go away. This is my home.

410
00:24:08,984 --> 00:24:14,783
I bought you
some lollipops on the way. Try one.

411
00:24:14,864 --> 00:24:15,543
No.

412
00:24:47,224 --> 00:24:48,503
Why didn't you hit me?

413
00:24:49,583 --> 00:24:50,464
Why would I hit you?

414
00:24:51,984 --> 00:24:53,080
I won't take your surname.

415
00:24:54,144 --> 00:24:56,103
Then don't.
We'll change it back tomorrow.

416
00:24:59,823 --> 00:25:04,023
Why don't you get angry?
Do you have no temper?

417
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:07,823
Of course I have a temper.
Everyone does.

418
00:25:08,303 --> 00:25:10,624
But you don't
take that temper out on your family.

419
00:25:11,583 --> 00:25:13,103
Take it out on whoever bullies you.

420
00:25:16,263 --> 00:25:17,263
Let me put it this way.

421
00:25:17,783 --> 00:25:21,664
If anyone bullies our family
or someone we care about,

422
00:25:22,023 --> 00:25:25,144
you do whatever it takes to fight back.

423
00:25:30,144 --> 00:25:31,103
Pick one.

424
00:25:34,864 --> 00:25:36,063
Good choice. It's the best.

425
00:25:37,303 --> 00:25:39,503
Stop crying. Let's go home.

426
00:25:39,884 --> 00:25:41,864
Get up. Hop on.

427
00:25:42,103 --> 00:25:45,384
Come on, hold on tight. Up you go.

428
00:25:46,624 --> 00:25:47,583
You're pretty heavy.

429
00:25:48,424 --> 00:25:50,224
- (I wouldn't take his surname.)
- Let's go home.

430
00:25:50,984 --> 00:25:54,543
(But I was willing to believe
that he would protect me.)

431
00:25:55,583 --> 00:25:58,063
(That was the first time I felt safe.)

432
00:26:11,448 --> 00:26:13,733
(1996)

433
00:26:13,848 --> 00:26:19,064
(2004)

434
00:26:21,592 --> 00:26:23,223
(Morgue)

435
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:51,000
(Award)

436
00:27:05,384 --> 00:27:06,984
(The moment I saw his body,)

437
00:27:07,144 --> 00:27:12,583
(I finally believed the man who made me
feel safe and talked to me was gone.)

438
00:27:13,583 --> 00:27:16,103
(Even if I meet
someone like him someday,)

439
00:27:16,503 --> 00:27:17,543
(it won't be him.)

440
00:27:18,543 --> 00:27:22,743
(He will forever be just
a black-and-white photo on the wall.)

441
00:27:24,904 --> 00:27:28,343
You refused to change your surname
to Qian and scratched the booklet.

442
00:27:28,984 --> 00:27:31,704
Why are you so reluctant
to change it back to my surname now?

443
00:27:37,583 --> 00:27:38,704
Ungrateful.

444
00:27:42,023 --> 00:27:42,664
I'll do it.

445
00:27:43,464 --> 00:27:44,704
How am I ungrateful?

446
00:27:50,144 --> 00:27:50,783
I'll do it.

447
00:27:51,823 --> 00:27:53,343
I bought that for Uncle Qian.

448
00:27:53,823 --> 00:27:54,583
But I paid for it.

449
00:27:55,664 --> 00:27:58,424
You want me
to cry all day and do nothing?

450
00:27:58,583 --> 00:28:00,864
Mourning by his photo
would make me loyal to him?

451
00:28:03,864 --> 00:28:05,984
If I cried all day, who would feed you?

452
00:28:06,343 --> 00:28:08,464
You're the ungrateful one here.

453
00:28:17,543 --> 00:28:19,063
What are you doing?

454
00:28:21,343 --> 00:28:22,424
Keep it down.

455
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:26,783
I've been working night shifts.
I'll die if I don't get some sleep.

456
00:28:30,783 --> 00:28:33,783
(For eight years,
he gave us a stable home)

457
00:28:34,224 --> 00:28:36,103
(and soothed the pain
in everyone's heart.)

458
00:28:37,103 --> 00:28:39,704
(After he left,
the imbalance came back.)

459
00:28:40,103 --> 00:28:43,583
(We started arguing again,
anxious just like before.)

460
00:28:44,184 --> 00:28:46,524
(Award)

461
00:28:48,424 --> 00:28:52,144
I went to deregister you today,
Qian Zhongshi.

462
00:28:56,743 --> 00:28:59,823
The kids will take my last name,
Ren, from now on.

463
00:29:00,664 --> 00:29:04,624
Wherever you are,
you have to watch over us.

464
00:29:11,224 --> 00:29:12,103
Die!

465
00:29:12,144 --> 00:29:14,704
What are you doing?

466
00:29:15,664 --> 00:29:16,904
Ren Xiaofei.

467
00:29:17,424 --> 00:29:18,063
What's wrong?

468
00:29:18,063 --> 00:29:18,823
Don't move!

469
00:29:20,503 --> 00:29:21,904
Xiaofei! Ren Xiaofei!

470
00:29:25,624 --> 00:29:26,783
I'll kill you!

471
00:29:28,984 --> 00:29:29,823
I'll kill you!

472
00:29:29,904 --> 00:29:31,103
Get the medicine.

473
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:33,704
I'll kill you!

474
00:29:37,263 --> 00:29:37,904
Hurry.

475
00:29:48,023 --> 00:29:49,523
Good boy, Xiaofei.

476
00:29:49,664 --> 00:29:51,664
Mom's here.

477
00:29:52,063 --> 00:29:53,263
Mom's right here.

478
00:29:54,343 --> 00:29:56,424
Good boy. Mom's here.

479
00:29:58,224 --> 00:29:59,823
He was just fine. How did it happen?

480
00:29:59,984 --> 00:30:00,823
What did you do?

481
00:30:02,343 --> 00:30:05,343
We were watching TV,
and he grabbed the remote from me.

482
00:30:05,343 --> 00:30:08,023
Why did you fight him?
You know he has a condition.

483
00:30:09,664 --> 00:30:12,343
I was watching it first.
Why should I give in to him?

484
00:30:12,464 --> 00:30:14,343
It's always "why" with you!

485
00:30:14,783 --> 00:30:16,408
Why should I work
night shifts every day?

486
00:30:16,864 --> 00:30:18,624
Why do I have to lecture you?

487
00:30:21,184 --> 00:30:22,904
What are you doing? Pick that up.

488
00:30:28,023 --> 00:30:28,904
What are you doing?

489
00:30:34,864 --> 00:30:35,823
What are you doing?

490
00:30:44,583 --> 00:30:46,743
Ren Xiaoming, get back here!

491
00:31:16,783 --> 00:31:17,583
What happened?

492
00:31:20,743 --> 00:31:25,023
People from the Qian family came.
They want the house back.

493
00:31:25,664 --> 00:31:27,384
We have two days to move out.

494
00:31:28,624 --> 00:31:29,743
Two days?

495
00:31:29,984 --> 00:31:31,984
If we don't move, they'll come again.

496
00:31:34,303 --> 00:31:35,224
I'll call the police.

497
00:31:35,224 --> 00:31:36,263
Come back.

498
00:31:40,664 --> 00:31:42,263
It's their house.

499
00:31:42,984 --> 00:31:47,783
They said that the three of us
wore him to death.

500
00:31:51,904 --> 00:31:56,503
Let's just pack up
and give them back the house.

501
00:31:59,424 --> 00:32:00,783
Help me up.

502
00:32:04,503 --> 00:32:05,224
Be gentle.

503
00:32:07,664 --> 00:32:08,263
Easy.

504
00:32:22,704 --> 00:32:23,543
Where is Xiaofei?

505
00:32:23,904 --> 00:32:26,503
He's asleep. Thanks to the medicine.

506
00:32:27,103 --> 00:32:27,984
I locked him in.

507
00:32:34,063 --> 00:32:38,864
I did pass a few people
when I stormed out.

508
00:32:40,864 --> 00:32:42,503
But I didn't know who they were.

509
00:32:43,303 --> 00:32:44,904
Luckily, you ran away.

510
00:32:46,424 --> 00:32:47,984
That's just my fate.

511
00:32:49,503 --> 00:32:52,823
I can't count on anyone
when trouble comes.

512
00:33:49,343 --> 00:33:51,944
(Uncle Qian, I'm leaving.)

513
00:33:53,424 --> 00:33:56,263
(Sorry, I can't take you with me.)

514
00:33:58,263 --> 00:34:02,864
(Our home is too small
to hold all the longing.)

515
00:34:04,543 --> 00:34:06,063
(I've never called you Dad.)

516
00:34:07,424 --> 00:34:09,183
(Because you're more important
than a dad.)

517
00:34:12,632 --> 00:34:13,849
(Award)

518
00:34:14,103 --> 00:34:15,703
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
It's his death anniversary, remember?

519
00:34:16,904 --> 00:34:18,904
Did you come here just to upset me?

520
00:34:24,103 --> 00:34:24,944
I brought you money.

521
00:34:26,583 --> 00:34:30,904
I wish my beautiful mother
a long life and prosperity,

522
00:34:31,103 --> 00:34:33,583
a happy marriage with kids soon.

523
00:34:34,464 --> 00:34:35,503
Thanks, sweetie.

524
00:34:36,103 --> 00:34:39,304
Everybody dies.
Live well while you're alive.

525
00:34:40,464 --> 00:34:42,183
The living matter more than the dead.

526
00:34:42,784 --> 00:34:44,744
Ren Meiyan, come on, photo time.

527
00:34:44,744 --> 00:34:45,264
Coming.

528
00:34:45,264 --> 00:34:46,143
Hurry up.

529
00:34:47,703 --> 00:34:49,904
Li, hurry up.

530
00:34:50,344 --> 00:34:52,744
(She's managed
to marry Zhao, Qian, Sun, and Li.)

531
00:34:52,744 --> 00:34:53,984
Come take a photo.

532
00:34:54,063 --> 00:34:55,103
- I'll pass.
- Come on.

533
00:34:55,864 --> 00:34:56,944
Come on.

534
00:35:00,543 --> 00:35:02,103
- So nice.
- So blessed.

535
00:35:11,944 --> 00:35:12,663
Ren Xiaofei.

536
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:19,663
Ren Xiaofei.

537
00:35:26,103 --> 00:35:28,623
Ren Xiaofei?

538
00:35:35,984 --> 00:35:38,344
Come out. I found you.

539
00:35:39,703 --> 00:35:42,264
Come out and pour me some water.

540
00:35:45,944 --> 00:35:47,503
Why didn't you go to Mom's wedding?

541
00:35:48,984 --> 00:35:49,984
I prefer the closet.

542
00:35:52,543 --> 00:35:53,264
Have some water.

543
00:35:53,583 --> 00:35:54,984
That old man didn't want you there?

544
00:35:56,583 --> 00:36:00,023
Uncle Li is really nice.
I didn't want to go.

545
00:36:06,384 --> 00:36:09,063
What are you holding? Snacks?

546
00:36:09,984 --> 00:36:11,284
Let me try some. Come on.

547
00:36:13,984 --> 00:36:14,583
Give it...

548
00:36:15,503 --> 00:36:18,264
What are you doing? Don't be so stingy.

549
00:36:21,183 --> 00:36:22,304
Fine, I won't eat it.

550
00:36:29,848 --> 00:36:33,447
(Will)

551
00:36:34,223 --> 00:36:35,063
A will?

552
00:36:36,063 --> 00:36:36,984
It's Mom's.

553
00:36:37,464 --> 00:36:40,063
I found it in the box under her bed.

554
00:36:40,663 --> 00:36:45,023
All assets are to be inherited
by Wen Yuxiu. Who is Wen Yuxiu?

555
00:36:45,183 --> 00:36:45,864
No idea.

556
00:36:49,623 --> 00:36:50,824
Let me cut your hair.

557
00:36:51,663 --> 00:36:52,920
I have to rush back tomorrow.

558
00:36:55,424 --> 00:36:57,384
Now that Mom's married,
where will they live?

559
00:36:57,824 --> 00:37:00,103
Mom will live here.
Uncle Li will stay at his place.

560
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:02,543
Married but not living together?
That's modern.

561
00:37:03,784 --> 00:37:05,744
How did you find Mom's will?

562
00:37:06,944 --> 00:37:07,503
Don't move.

563
00:37:09,864 --> 00:37:13,944
Late last night,
I heard Mom crying in the bathroom.

564
00:37:14,864 --> 00:37:16,264
So I got up to take a look.

565
00:37:17,183 --> 00:37:18,864
She was holding that piece of paper.

566
00:37:20,103 --> 00:37:21,464
Has she been doing square dancing?

567
00:37:22,663 --> 00:37:23,183
Yeah.

568
00:37:23,503 --> 00:37:24,623
And singing?

569
00:37:25,344 --> 00:37:25,844
Yeah.

570
00:37:27,543 --> 00:37:31,023
Then she should be fine.
Why did she write a will?

571
00:37:33,784 --> 00:37:35,583
And who exactly is Wen Yuxiu?

572
00:37:36,703 --> 00:37:37,904
You don't know?

573
00:37:38,384 --> 00:37:40,824
Even you don't know. How would I know?

574
00:37:44,183 --> 00:37:45,944
Probably a woman, right?

575
00:37:48,183 --> 00:37:49,264
Not necessarily.

576
00:37:51,023 --> 00:37:52,663
There are so many scammers.

577
00:37:53,744 --> 00:37:55,864
Our mom is materialistic
and easily swayed.

578
00:37:56,944 --> 00:38:00,063
What if some old guy cons her
out of money and affection?

579
00:38:01,304 --> 00:38:02,264
Some old guy?

580
00:38:04,103 --> 00:38:07,183
You said you needed a table
to host your guests.

581
00:38:07,424 --> 00:38:11,703
I don't care about the numbers,
but not a single person showed up?

582
00:38:13,063 --> 00:38:14,464
This is disrespectful.

583
00:38:19,103 --> 00:38:22,063
Call all of them.
Ask for an explanation.

584
00:38:27,183 --> 00:38:27,904
I will do it.

585
00:38:30,552 --> 00:38:32,944
(Groom's guests)

586
00:38:32,944 --> 00:38:34,023
Forget it.

587
00:38:35,304 --> 00:38:39,784
Well, I didn't tell anyone
that I was getting married.

588
00:38:40,264 --> 00:38:44,063
So all this fanfare from me,
and you were working underground?

589
00:38:45,023 --> 00:38:47,503
Li Wancheng. Li Wancheng!

590
00:38:49,944 --> 00:38:51,824
Please don't shout. Everyone's looking.

591
00:38:52,623 --> 00:38:54,824
So what if they look at me? Come on.

592
00:38:57,424 --> 00:38:58,944
Here! Have a look!

593
00:38:59,304 --> 00:39:02,023
We got the marriage certificate.
It's right and legal.

594
00:39:02,424 --> 00:39:05,703
Enough. They know it's right and legal.

595
00:39:06,744 --> 00:39:09,023
You wanted to get married,
so we got the paper.

596
00:39:09,623 --> 00:39:11,344
You wanted a wedding, and you got one.

597
00:39:12,663 --> 00:39:16,103
But at our age,

598
00:39:16,464 --> 00:39:20,543
everyone has some historical baggage.

599
00:39:21,063 --> 00:39:22,984
What do you mean? Make it clear.

600
00:39:24,424 --> 00:39:25,784
Your son disapproves of it?

601
00:39:26,183 --> 00:39:27,703
Did you marry me secretly?

602
00:39:30,304 --> 00:39:33,183
Make up your mind. Tell your kids.

603
00:39:33,744 --> 00:39:37,223
Get me the gift money,
and we'll live together.

604
00:39:38,623 --> 00:39:41,264
Or meet me at the Civil Affairs Bureau
at 9:00 AM tomorrow.

605
00:39:42,663 --> 00:39:43,264
Come on.

606
00:39:43,264 --> 00:39:45,663
Kids, stop staring.
Pack up the leftovers.

607
00:39:45,984 --> 00:39:46,784
Pack everything.

608
00:39:47,384 --> 00:39:49,824
This, this, and this. Pack everything.

609
00:40:00,063 --> 00:40:02,464
Jeez, what now?

610
00:40:11,583 --> 00:40:14,264
You look refreshed.
You finally did something decent.

611
00:40:14,703 --> 00:40:16,623
I packed you so much nice food.

612
00:40:23,703 --> 00:40:26,583
Mom, who is Wen Yuxiu?

613
00:40:50,304 --> 00:40:52,023
You even pick locks at home too?

614
00:40:52,703 --> 00:40:54,103
Picking locks out there is illegal.

615
00:41:06,626 --> 00:41:08,984
(Will)

616
00:41:08,984 --> 00:41:09,944
Who is Wen Yuxiu?

617
00:41:13,543 --> 00:41:15,824
Why are you leaving everything
to a stranger?

618
00:41:32,744 --> 00:41:33,904
None of your business.

619
00:41:58,296 --> 00:42:02,612
(Will)

620
00:42:35,768 --> 00:42:38,648
(Ren Meiyan, Wen Yuxiu,
Youyi Photo Studio, July 1987)

621
00:42:52,583 --> 00:42:54,104
(An unidentified body was discovered)

622
00:42:54,104 --> 00:42:56,784
(at the demolition site
of Qidian Middle School.)

623
00:42:57,063 --> 00:42:59,503
(We are now appealing
to the public for information.)

624
00:42:59,663 --> 00:43:03,344
(Contact Municipal Police at 110
with any relevant information.)

625
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
